posts.title: Amazed monke
posts.description: Monkey Puppet, also known as the Awkward Look Monkey, refers to a reaction image and GIF of a puppet appearing surprised. It's used to express shock, particularly in situations where one party owns another in a verbal exchange.

posts.title: Dead monke
posts.description: Just monke after long and exhausting day

posts.title: Haircut monke
posts.description: Monkey Haircut is a viral video of a young macaque monkey closing its eyes while receiving a haircut. Online, the video spawned a photoshop meme in which a screen capture from the video is superimposed into other base images to appear as if a variety of people and characters are cutting the monkey's hair.

posts.title: Programmer monke
posts.description: Every student who's learning react right now

posts.title: Monke Sony Walkman
posts.description: Monkey Sony Walkman refers to a Sony Walkman advertisement video in which a monkey known as Choromatsu listens to music using a Walkman. Online, the video has been paired with a variety of songs, depicting the monkey listening to the music in question.

posts.title: Where banana
posts.description: Where Banana refers to a photoshopped image taken from a 2017 episode of BBC Breakfast showing three orangutans sitting around a coffee table, the orangutan farthest to the right saying, 'where banana.' The image became popular in image macros, photoshops, and as an exploitable over the following years.

posts.title: Monke wearing coat
posts.description: IKEA Monkey is the nickname given to a Japanese snow macaque named Darwin that was found loose wearing a coat at a Canadian IKEA store in December of 2012.
